So there are a couple issues.

12:03.028 --> 12:04.770
Wow, that's complex.

12:05.196 --> 12:07.031
That is [bleep] complex.

12:07.065 --> 12:09.833
Um, your daughter is trying
to have a conversation

12:09.868 --> 12:11.535
with you, so if you could
put the cookie down,

12:11.569 --> 12:13.727
and try to engage meaningfully...

12:14.672 --> 12:17.141
I'm so sorry, I was just
recently in couple's therapy,

12:17.175 --> 12:18.600
and that just popped out.

12:20.078 --> 12:22.880
All right, I'm engaging meaningfully.

12:23.948 --> 12:26.395
I don't want to do a Green Day party.

12:26.718 --> 12:28.252
I thought I asked you to
mind your own business.

12:28.286 --> 12:30.242
This is all Cheyenne,
I'm just here for support.

12:30.243 --> 12:32.423
But she agrees with me, okay?

12:32.457 --> 12:33.757
Green Day is dumb.

12:33.792 --> 12:36.693
And you know what?
I'm not going to college.

12:36.728 --> 12:38.929
What? Huh?
No, we didn't talk about that.

12:38.963 --> 12:40.164
Cheyenne, you're going to college.

12:40.198 --> 12:40.958
No, I'm not.

12:41.243 --> 12:42.699
Just 'cause you're my
mom doesn't mean that

12:42.734 --> 12:44.101
you get to tell me what to do.

12:44.135 --> 12:45.119
Right, Amy?

12:45.120 --> 12:49.039
Um, I mean, in general,
that seems true...

12:49.074 --> 12:50.340
See? She agrees.

12:50.375 --> 12:52.876
I'm an adult, and I
make my own decisions.

12:52.911 --> 12:55.546
And so, I'm gonna buy a motorcycle,

12:55.580 --> 12:58.115
or, I don't know, a monkey, maybe both.

12:58.149 --> 13:00.717
Um, could we just quickly
go back to the college thing...

13:00.752 --> 13:02.286
You don't get to tell
me what to eat, either!

13:02.320 --> 13:03.854
So if I want to eat peyote,

13:03.888 --> 13:05.789
I am gonna eat all the peyote I want.

13:05.824 --> 13:08.192
And I'm getting a full-sized back tattoo

13:08.226 --> 13:10.727
of the raccoon from
"Guardians of the Galaxy,"

13:10.762 --> 13:13.664
okay? 'Cause I love that movie, and...

13:24.901 --> 13:27.302
So you're saying reindeers
actually exist,

13:27.337 --> 13:28.904
like, in the real world?

13:28.938 --> 13:31.373
We had a reindeer in the
store on Christmas.

13:31.407 --> 13:33.308
I didn't think it was a real reindeer.

13:33.343 --> 13:34.576
I thought it was a normal deer

13:34.610 --> 13:36.712
with antlers nailed to its head.

13:36.746 --> 13:39.981
Oh, I don't think leprechauns
should be in the real column.

13:40.016 --> 13:41.316
Who knows, though, right?

13:41.351 --> 13:42.818
- What?
- What are you doing?

13:42.852 --> 13:44.486
Is this still about the angel thing?

13:44.520 --> 13:46.555
- Hm?
- Look, I get it.

13:46.589 --> 13:48.623
I mean, it must be hard
to believe in angels

13:48.658 --> 13:50.325
if you've never seen one first-hand.

13:50.360 --> 13:53.095
Wait, you've seen an angel?

13:53.129 --> 13:54.679
- Sure have.
- When?

13:54.680 --> 13:56.965
Shh! When?

13:56.999 --> 13:59.634
Well, um, when I was five,

13:59.669 --> 14:01.603
I fell into the indoor pool

14:01.637 --> 14:03.171
at the Silver Dollar City Ramada Inn.

14:03.206 --> 14:04.339
And I mean,

14:04.374 --> 14:06.241
I sank like a brick.

14:06.275 --> 14:09.845
And I remember thinking I'd
never seen my parents again.

14:09.879 --> 14:12.914
When suddenly, this figure appeared.

14:12.949 --> 14:14.282
Did he have wings?

14:14.317 --> 14:15.350
He did have wings.

14:15.385 --> 14:16.752
Knew it. I knew it.

14:16.786 --> 14:19.354
And he sort of was like
floating above me,

14:19.389 --> 14:22.625
as if to say, "You're safe now."

14:23.059 --> 14:25.994
Next thing I know, I'm
back in our hotel room,

14:26.028 --> 14:27.302
dry as a bone.

14:27.830 --> 14:28.864
Oh!

14:28.898 --> 14:30.165
Wow.

14:30.199 --> 14:32.501
That's real.

14:32.535 --> 14:36.304
Is it possible that
the figure was floating

14:36.339 --> 14:39.040
because he was, you know, in a pool?

14:39.075 --> 14:40.709
I know what I saw.

14:40.743 --> 14:44.212
Yeah, and I believe that
you believe that you saw that,

14:44.247 --> 14:48.283
but you were also deprived of
oxygen for a little while...

14:48.317 --> 14:49.500
Why are you doing this?

14:49.501 --> 14:51.853
Because he's jelly
of your peanut butter.

14:51.888 --> 14:55.056
No, no, no, no, no.
I'm not... I'm not jelly, no.

14:55.091 --> 14:58.193
I just... I just think, you know,
maybe what you saw

14:58.227 --> 14:59.740
wasn't, um, an angel.

14:59.741 --> 15:04.618
Maybe what you saw was just
a pasty hotel guest in a robe.

15:05.268 --> 15:06.285
Yeah, maybe.

15:06.669 --> 15:08.370
Mm-hmm. Maybe I'll consider that

15:08.404 --> 15:10.405
when I'm home this weekend, alone.

15:10.440 --> 15:12.934
Whoa, whoa, what are
we talking about, now?

15:13.543 --> 15:15.710
Trouble in paradise.

15:15.745 --> 15:17.546
Have you been in the break room all day?

15:17.580 --> 15:19.581
Yeah, I'm just not feeling it today.

15:19.615 --> 15:22.050
Look, I'm sorry, I did not know that

15:22.084 --> 15:23.385
she was gonna say those things.

15:23.419 --> 15:25.320
All I said to her was that
she should be able

15:25.354 --> 15:27.489
to make her own decisions.
But I am not her mom.

15:27.523 --> 15:30.258
And if someone told my
daughter not to listen to me,

15:30.293 --> 15:32.194
well, then, I would be pretty upset.

15:32.228 --> 15:34.262
So, I am sorry.

15:34.297 --> 15:35.530
I just get so worried

15:35.565 --> 15:37.065
she's gonna make
the same mistakes I did.

15:37.099 --> 15:38.667
- Yeah.
- I get so scared

15:38.701 --> 15:40.101
she's gonna end up in jail,

15:40.136 --> 15:43.205
or still working here
when she's our age.

15:43.239 --> 15:44.673
Uh, yeah, I don't...

15:44.707 --> 15:47.108
I don't know that those two
are exactly equivalent.

15:47.143 --> 15:48.376
I don't know which is worse.

15:48.411 --> 15:50.278
Jail, probably.

15:50.313 --> 15:51.422
Well...

15:53.316 --> 15:55.147
Hey, what do you think about Bo?

15:55.585 --> 16:00.288
Uh, I think he is an
interesting individual.

16:00.323 --> 16:01.289
I think he's a loser.

16:01.324 --> 16:03.358
Clown. I mean, "clown"

16:03.392 --> 16:05.427
is the first word that comes to mind.

16:05.461 --> 16:06.795
When I think of him, like,

16:06.829 --> 16:09.564
I half expect my hand to
buzz when he shakes it.

16:09.599 --> 16:11.933
I don't think clowns do that any more,

16:11.968 --> 16:13.201
but that's very funny.

16:13.236 --> 16:14.238
You're funny.

16:16.515 --> 16:17.200
Hey.

16:18.674 --> 16:20.942
Dina, I know things
got a little heated...

16:20.977 --> 16:23.271
Listen, I apologize if I overreacted.

16:23.679 --> 16:25.981
Oh, thank God. Me too.

16:26.015 --> 16:27.883
The things is, I'm gonna go have sex

16:27.917 --> 16:28.984
- with Marcus in a few minutes.
- What?

16:28.985 --> 16:30.886
What?

16:30.920 --> 16:32.988
That's the special project
you needed help with?

16:33.786 --> 16:34.422
Sweet!

16:34.457 --> 16:36.224
- Why would you...
- There's just an attraction

16:36.259 --> 16:37.425
there, I can't deny it,

16:37.460 --> 16:38.581
blah, blah, blah, the point is,

16:38.582 --> 16:40.295
maybe I get pregnant, maybe I don't.

16:40.329 --> 16:41.237
Who knows?

16:41.238 --> 16:42.733
So this could be all booked up.

16:42.734 --> 16:43.990
No room at the inn.

16:43.991 --> 16:44.756
You can't do this.

16:44.757 --> 16:48.670
Oh, I am going to with zero protection.

16:48.704 --> 16:49.886
Zero?

16:50.706 --> 16:51.973
Amy and I think you need

16:52.008 --> 16:54.009
to start getting serious
about your life.

16:54.043 --> 16:55.744
So now you're on her side?

16:55.778 --> 16:57.979
No, I'm not on anyone's side.

16:58.014 --> 17:00.348
I just agree with her on this stuff.

17:00.383 --> 17:05.119
So, now I think it's time for
you to engage meaningfully.

17:05.154 --> 17:07.989
You gotta be responsible,
and part of being responsible

17:08.023 --> 17:09.124
means getting rid of Bo.

17:09.157 --> 17:10.162
Wait, what?

17:10.163 --> 17:11.792
He's a loser, Amy and I both agree.

17:11.827 --> 17:12.761
You do?

17:12.795 --> 17:15.530
No, uh-uh, I did never call him a loser.

17:15.565 --> 17:17.198
Sorry, I think I'm the one
who called him a loser.

17:17.233 --> 17:18.640
Amy called him a clown.

17:18.641 --> 17:20.669
I don't... I don't know
how this is productive.

17:20.703 --> 17:21.703
How about we get back to the college...

17:21.737 --> 17:23.278
I can't believe you guys.

17:23.973 --> 17:26.940
Amy and I are on the same
page about this one.

17:27.910 --> 17:29.644
I felt like that went so well.

17:29.679 --> 17:31.531
She is so attached to Bo.

17:32.315 --> 17:34.950
Yeah, they are married.

17:38.434 --> 17:39.685
The same rules as last time?

17:39.686 --> 17:42.291
No kissimg, no eye contact, I
leave as soon as you're done?

17:42.337 --> 17:43.670
We're not sleeping together.

17:43.705 --> 17:45.806
That was just a negotiation
tactic with Glenn.

17:45.840 --> 17:48.275
Oh, right.

17:48.797 --> 17:50.611
Of course. Smart.

17:51.171 --> 17:52.571
I mean, if someone actually cared,

17:52.606 --> 17:55.174
it could be super
hurtful, but it's not me.

17:55.208 --> 17:58.043
Dina, I'd like you to
meet my new surrogate.

17:58.078 --> 17:59.209
She's ready to rock.

17:59.210 --> 18:00.442
Isn't that right, Sandra?

18:00.443 --> 18:02.485
Yeah, I'm really excited.

18:03.083 --> 18:05.539
And I have no problem
signing all the paperwork,

18:05.540 --> 18:07.319
so let's do it.

18:07.354 --> 18:09.426
Sandra, mm-hmm.
You're gonna go with Sandra?

18:09.427 --> 18:10.157
Mm-hmm.

18:10.158 --> 18:12.381
You are gonna leave your baby
at the mercy of a person

18:12.382 --> 18:15.861
